==Romanian==
===Etymology===
From a neolithic root '''''[[*mal]]''''' 'mountain' found in Balkanic and Dravidian languages:
Albanese ''[[mal]]'' 'mount', Tamil ''[[malai]]'' 'hill', Malayälam ''[[mala]]'' 'mountain'...

Cf. Romanian ''[[mal]]'' 'sea shore', Ukrainian ''[[mul]]''
===Noun===
'''mâl''' pl ''[[mâluri]]''
#A type of granular sediment found near water or under water.

